-- Banks up after report on FDIC
-- 
-- Wed Jan 28, 2009 8:11am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/28/us-markets-stocks-beforethebell-idUSTRE50R3FU20090128

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of large-cap banks rose on Wednesday after Bloomberg News reported that the FDIC may take control of a U.S. "bad bank." 

 Citigroup ( C.N ) gained 20 percent to $4.25 while Bank of America ( BAC.N ) added 14.5 percent to $7.44 and JPMorgan Chase ( JPM.N ) was up 8.1 percent to $27.08. (Reporting by  Ryan Vlastelica ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)